org.openbel.framework.core.kamstore.model.dialect
Class KamDialect

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.core.kamstore.model.dialect.KamDialect
All Implemented Interfaces:
Kam, KamStoreObject
public final class KamDialect
extends Object
implements Kam

A KamDialect applies a Dialect to a KamNodes as needed.
When KamNodes are returned, the concrete object will be a wrapper around the original KamNode that applies the Dialect to generate a different label. Implementation considerations:

  • New wrapper objects are instantiated for every KamNode and KamEdge returned. This prevents additional memory requirements if a reference to the KamDialect is maintained by the user. There is additional young generation memory needs that may be tweaked with changes to gc if needed.
  • The Dialect is queried for every call to KamNode#getLabel() is made. This allows Dialect implementations to provide caching if desired without introducing additional memory overhead.
  • This implementation assumes NodeFilters and EdgeFilters do not perform any actions on the node labels. If/when this is changed, this implementation must be modified to account for filters that now need access to the label generated by the Dialect.

Author:
Steve Ungerer
